HEADWORD: phenotype
<hw>phenotype</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biology)</fld> <def>The
observable characteristics of an organism, resulting from the genetic
characteristics influenced by a particular environment. Contrasted with
<contr>genotype</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

